      "span_text": "Like the in-between test, the tactile localization task is thought to reflect higher level processing of finger gnosis [CITATION_1] , however, in this task participants performance will reflect judgments only of the localization of touch and therefore of the representations of the two fingers touched rather than a more extensive part of the hand, including also the fingers in-between the fingers touched."
